# config.env.example — local machine configuration for the shell scripts.
#
# Copy this file to scripts/config.env and edit the values for your machine:
#
#     cp scripts/config.env.example scripts/config.env
#
# Each script automatically sources scripts/config.env if it exists (it is
# optional). Any variable you leave unset falls back to a sensible default:
# the repo-root variables are derived from the script's own location, the HF
# cache defaults to ~/.cache/huggingface, and the Python interpreter defaults
# to whatever `python` is on your PATH. The only variable with NO safe default
# is SIF — the Singularity scripts will refuse to run until it is set.
#
# NOTE: config.env is machine-specific and should NOT be committed to git.
#       Add `scripts/config.env` to your .gitignore.

# ── Repo root ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Absolute path to the checked-out repository. If unset, each script derives
# this from its own location, so you normally do not need to set it.
# PROJ_DIR="/path/to/misfired-alignment"

# ── Fast scratch copy of the repo (optional) ──────────────────────────────
# Some clusters offer a faster local/scratch filesystem. Point this at a
# scratch checkout of the repo if you have one; otherwise it defaults to
# PROJ_DIR (no separate scratch copy).
# SCRATCH_DIR="/scratch/path/to/misfired-alignment"

# ── HuggingFace model cache ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Directory used as HF_HOME for local model downloads/inference.
# Defaults to $HOME/.cache/huggingface.
# HF_HOME="$HOME/.cache/huggingface"

# ── Singularity image (REQUIRED for the Singularity-based scripts) ─────────
# Absolute path to the Singularity/Apptainer .sif image that provides the
# CUDA + transformers runtime. There is no safe default; scripts that need it
# will error out if it is unset.
# SIF="/path/to/verl_vllm018.dev1.sif"

# ── Python interpreter ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Path to the Python used by the non-Singularity scripts. Defaults to the
# `python` on your PATH (e.g. your active conda/venv environment).
# PYTHON="python"
